The program 'add' takes two hexadecimal strings in input and output the sum a + b * n
to make test easier we made a python script which take three agrument : a, b, n or the argument 'big' to do the test suggested in the orginial readme.
The script test our implementation then check is with 'checkadd' and finaly give the time of the 'badadd' run.


add [n] : read the two integer in heaxadecimal string from the input and output a + b * n
          with the addition done n times and give the result in a hexadecimal string

addtest.py a b n [ibase] : take two string of integer in base 'ibase' if given or 10 by default
                           and call add / checkadd / badadd with there parameters to test
                           speed and correctness of add.
                           it ouput the result in base 10

addtest.py big           : this default one argument call does the same as : 
                           addtest.py 174316498273647891264182764916 138971038947123471239048723 1000000
